#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:43
msgid "Create an SSH key pair"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:45
msgid ""
"The *local machine*'s Nix daemon runs as the `root` user and will need the "
"*private* key file to authenticate itself to remote machines. The *remote "
"machine* will need the *public* key to recognize the *local machine*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:48
msgid ""
"On the *local machine*, run the following command as `root` to create an SSH "
"key pair:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:50
msgid "# ssh-keygen -f /root/.ssh/remotebuild\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:55
msgid "The name and location of the key pair files can be freely chosen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:59
msgid "Set up the remote builder"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:61
msgid ""
"In the NixOS configuration directory of the *remote machine*, create the "
"file `remote-builder.nix`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:63
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  users.users.remotebuild = {\n"
"    isSystemUser = true;\n"
"    group = \"remotebuild\";\n"
"    useDefaultShell = true;\n"
"\n"
"    openssh.authorizedKeys.keyFiles = [ ./remotebuild.pub ];\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"  users.groups.remotebuild = {};\n"
"\n"
"  nix.settings.trusted-users = [ \"remotebuild\" ];\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:79
msgid "Copy the file `remotebuild.pub` into this directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:81
msgid ""
"This configuration module creates a new user `remotebuild` with no home "
"directory. The `root` user on the *local machine* will be able to log into "
"the remote builder via SSH using the previously generated SSH key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:84
msgid ""
"Add the new NixOS module to the existing configuration of the *remote "
"machine*:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:86
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  imports = [\n"
"    ./remote-builder.nix\n"
"  ];\n"
"\n"
"  # ...\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:96
msgid "Activate the new configuration as root:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:98
msgid "nixos-rebuild switch --no-flake --target-host root@remotemachine\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:102
msgid "Test authentication"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:104
msgid ""
"Make sure that the SSH connection and authentication work. On the *local "
"machine*, run as `root`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:107
msgid ""
"# ssh remotebuild@remotemachine -i /root/.ssh/remotebuild \"echo hello\"\n"
"hello\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:112
msgid "If the `hello` message is visible, the authentication works."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:114
msgid ""
"This test login also adds the host key of the remote builder to the `/root/."
"ssh/known_hosts` file of the local machine. Future logins will not be "
"interrupted by host key checks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/nixos/distributed-builds-setup.md:118
msgid "Set up distributed builds"
